Metasoma
. Tergal process with deep, subtriangular and sublateral pair of depressions; depressions with external lateral margin higher than internal lateral margin, 0.83 × as long as tergite II, diverging posterad, distant on top with short and dorsad tuft of setae (
Figs 27–30
). Hypopygium with median stalk 1.15 × as long as hypopygeal plate; median stalk narrow; corner of anterior margin angular; lateral stalk of hypopygium 0.11 × as long as median stalk; posterior margin strongly concave; corner angalute (
Fig. 104
).
